Set:
	Set is an Interface in Java extends the Collection Interface.
	Set represent unordered collections that does not allow duplicate elements and no positional access.
	Set is a Single dimensional collection
	
Common implementation classes of Set Interface:
	1. HashSet	
			--> HashSet is a re-sizable array implementation of the Set interface
			--> Insertion order not maintained
			--> Duplicates not allowed
			--> Allows to add  null value
			--> Data stored based on Hash code , so search is very effective
			--> Not synchronized
			--> Heterogeneous is allowed if generic is not specified  
	2. LinkedHashSet	
			--> LinkedHashSet is a re-sizable array implementation of the Set interface
			--> Insertion order maintained
			--> Duplicates not allowed
			--> Allows to add  null value
			--> Heterogeneous is allowed if generic is not specified
	3. TreeSet	
			--> TreeSet is a re-sizable array implementation of the SortedSet and Navigatableset interface
			--> Natural sorting order maintained
			--> Duplicates not allowed
			--> Null not allows
			--> Heterogeneous is not allowed even if generic is not specified	
